I do know<br>
<br>
A level 20 and a level 8 group together.  Were this EQ, it wouldn't really float very far.  IE:  Even if the level 20 killed soemthing that gave EXP to him, the level 8 wouldn't get EXP as long as they're grouped.<br>
<br>
DAoC doesn't work this way though.  Apparently, no matter what the level difference, it is possible for any spread of levels to get EXP together.<br>
<br>
The only rule is, the monster you kill cannot be grey to the highest member of the group, if the mob is grey to anyone in the group, it does not give exp or drop items.<br>
<br>
Do any other Beta-testers know some more details about it?  Such as exp bonus' for grouping and such?<br>
<br>
Any opinions on what is posted so far?<br>
