<br>
Generally speaking, you are correct Draeven. Any level can group with any level and get exp so long as the mob is not grey to the highest level group member. Haemish, you are also correct. Killing blues and greens solo is fine, though slower than killing with a good group. Killing blues and greens in a group is really a waste of time if you're looking to level.<br>
<br>
Here are a few combinations that come to mind that I've tried. All were with my Albion Cleric. Note that there is an experience cap per mob based on level. Thus, while a level 20 might get 135000 exp for a mob, if he's grouped with a level 10, the level 10 may only get 16000 off the same mob.<br>
<br>
At level 11, I went to Avalon Marsh with a group levels 18 to 23. Two hours later, I dinged level 14.<br>
<br>
At level 18, I grouped in a full group of similar levels except we added a level 6 Bard for the Speed and Rest songs. We played long enough for me to make 19 (2 hours maybe?) and in that time the Bard had made level 9.<br>
<br>
At level 20, I grouped with a full group levels 36 to 43. We hunted for about an hour before encountering and engaging a group of Middies. I gained about 40% of my level during that hour. The Middies won that one :-/.<br>
<br>
I think it's fairly conclusive that if it's a friend, group with them, levels be damned. You do have to adjust to accomodate them, of course. Even had the level 6 Bard been trying to melee, for instance, he'd have added virtually no damage output. The two high level groups knew I couldn't keep up with the heavy damage of the mobs they wanted to fight. They wanted me along to try, though, and mostly to rez. Almost every time I group far above my level, they tell me to use all my power to heal, then immediately run away in case the fight goes bad. There's been a couple of times it worked exactly as intended, too... I was alive to rez the rest of the group in its entirety.<br>
<br>
I've grouped &quot;out of range&quot; several other times with similar results.. these were just times that popped to mind.<br>
<br>
Dog<br>
