in groups</span><hr size=1> The camp bonus is given for areas where the mobs have been up for a while. Basically, if Mob A is up for all of 5 seconds before someone comes along and ganks him, you get no camp bonus. If you go to camp B where Mob B has been up for 2-3 hours without being attacked and killed, you get a camp bonus of like 20-30%. Part of Mythic's anti-camping code, to encourage you to move out and fight someplace you've never been. <br>
<br>
Also, some mobs are labeled as scouts. When you select them, they will say &quot;Basilisk is aggressive and is a scout.&quot; What that means is that most of the time, when you hit this mob, he won't follow you... instead, he'll run the other direction, looking for friends, and then bring the whole party back to you. <br>
<br>
